	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60753><span id= >Soop</span></a><br><span id=notbold>113 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Actually, when this happens is when you zone with fewer hitpoints than the hitpoints added by your armor.&nbsp;&nbsp;So in effect you do die because the armor hp drop off at zone then come back on the other side.  <br><br>Lets say you have on 2 55hp rings.  you zone with sow and 25hp.  Upon entering the zone the ring hp drop taking your hp to zero, in effect killing you and taking away your buffs, yet when you zone in, the rings take effect again giving you 110 hp instead of 25 hp when you get to the other side and you nolonger have sow.<br><br>It is a pretty good trade off unless you are one of those melee types who wait way too long to zone and dont have the ability to rebuff because you had that very nice shaman mojo all over you, but she is now long gone and you are back to dukeing it out with your normal bad self.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Soop 53ish War<br>Brell<br><br>Pugette Tripsalott<br>61 Monk&nbsp;&nbsp;- Brell<br><br>Raynn Fahling<br>55 Druid - Brell</td></tr>
